  "prompt": "What percentage of the world population is religious?",
  "response": "As of 2021, estimates suggested that around 84% of the world's population identified with some form of religious belief. This includes various major religions such as Christianity, Islam, Hinduism, Buddhism, and others, as well as indigenous and folk religions. The secular or non-religious population\u2014including atheists, agnostics, and those who identify as spiritual but not religious\u2014makes up the remaining 16%. However, this data can vary by source and region, and it may have changed slightly since then. For the most current statistics, it's always a good idea to refer to reputable surveys or studies on religious demographics.",
